Here is the Video showing Nigeria’s Oluwatobiloba Amusan as she makes history as the first Nigerian to win 100m hurdles gold at commonwealth games. She finished the race in 12.68 seconds. Amusan defeated Jamaica’s duo of Danielle Willimas and Yanique Thompson who finished on 12.78 and 12.97 seconds respectively. Team Nigeria recorded a total of four gold medals on Day Nine. The Games which began on April 4 will end on Saturday. Watch the video as posted by @d_problemsolver: 